contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary|Olympian|Olympians}} '''Olympian''' or '''Olympians''' may refer to: {{toc right}} {{tocright}} == Sport == * A participant in the [[Olympic Games]] * [[SoCal Olympians]], an organization of the United States Olympic team * [[London Olympians]], a British amateur American football team based in Beckenham, London * [[Beijing Olympians]], a Chinese professional men's basketball team * [[Indianapolis Olympians]], a National Basketball Association (NBA) team based in Indianapolis, Indiana, USA from 1949 to 1953 * [[World Olympians Association]], an association of former Olympic athletes from all over the world == Technology == * [[Olympian (automobile)]], an automobile built by the Olympian Motors Company from 1917-21 * [[Olympian (sidewheeler)|''Olympian'' (sidewheeler)]], a large sidewheel steamboat that operated on Puget Sound from about 1884 to 1890 * [[Leyland Olympian]], a double-decker bus built by British Leyland/Leyland Bus * [[Leyland-MCW Olympian]], a single-deck bus built by Weymann Coachbuilders using Leyland Tiger Cub units * [[Volvo Olympian]], a rear-engine double decker bus built by Volvo from 1992 to 2000 * Volvo Olympian (low-floor) or [[Volvo B9TL]], a low-floor double-decker bus built by Volvo Buses since 2002 * ''Olympian'' and ''[[Olympian Hiawatha]]'', passenger trains operated by the Chicago, Milwaukee, St. Paul and Pacific Railroad from 1911 to 1961 * Olympian (typeface), a typeface designed in 1970 by [[Matthew Carter]] == Literature and mythology == * [[Olympians (Marvel Comics)]], a fictional species in the Marvel Comics universe, based loosely on the Twelve Olympians and other deities of Greek mythology * [[Olympian (comics)]], a superhero from DC Comics * [[Olympian Gods (DC Comics)]], characters based upon Greek mythology who appear primarily in Wonder Woman, Captain Marvel and Aquaman * The [[Twelve Olympians]], leaders of the Gods in Ancient Greek mythology * ''[[Percy Jackson & the Olympians]]'', a series of adventure and fiction books written by Rick Riordan * [[Olympian spirits]], spirits mentioned in several renaissance and post-renaissance books of magic == Places == * [[Olympian High School]], a public high school in San Diego County, California * [[Olympian City]], a shopping and residential complex on the reclaimed land of Tai Kok Tsui, Kowloon, Hong Kong * Citizens of [[Olympia, Washington]] * Citizens of the ancient Greek city-state of [[Olympia, Greece]] == Other uses == * [[Olympian (album)|''Olympian'' (album)]], an album by British rock band Gene * ''[[The Olympian]]'', a daily newspaper based in Olympia, Washington * ''[[The Olympians]]'', an opera by Arthur Bliss to a libretto by J. B. Priestley, first performed in 1949 * [[Olympian Publishing]], a publishing house with offices in Chicago, IL, USA * [[Committee of 300]], a conspiracy theory which alleges the existence of a group founded by the British aristocracy in 1727 {{disambiguation}}
